    <abstract>
      <p><bold>Summary:</bold> We present <italic>bammds</italic>, a practical tool that allows visualization of samples sequenced by second-generation sequencing when compared with a reference panel of individuals (usually genotypes) using a multidimensional scaling algorithm. Our tool is aimed at determining the ancestry of unknown samples—typical of ancient DNA data—particularly when only low amounts of data are available for those samples.</p>
      <p><bold>Availability and implementation:</bold> The software package is available under GNU General Public License v3 and is freely available together with test datasets <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/bammds/">https://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/bammds/</ext-link>. It is using R (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.r-project.org/">http://www.r-project.org/</ext-link>), parallel (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.gnu.org/software/parallel/">http://www.gnu.org/software/parallel/</ext-link>), samtools (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/samtools/samtools">https://github.com/samtools/samtools</ext-link>).</p>
